Free energy is not testable
text: Friston himself says that because it is a principle and not a theory, free energy cannot be falsified: “It cannot be disproven. In fact, there’s not much you can do with it, unless you ask whether measurable systems conform to the principle.” He even suggests that his principle might be a “nihilistic tautology”. Ref: Friston, K., Fortier, M. & Friedman, D. A. (2018). Of woodlice and men: A Bayesian account of cognition, life and consciousness. An interview with Karl Friston. ALIUS Bulletin, 2, 17-43.
